11. 28-30. Note the condensation of ideas in these two lines. Achilles was famous, but death came quick. Tithonus lived long, but he wasted in a long old age.

Tithonus, a mortal, wedded the Dawn goddess and asked of her immortality. She gave it him, but not perpetual youth, so he lived on, ‘ Immortal age beside immortal youth)
